==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[allusio]]''' ''f'', from '''[[alludere]]''', ''allude'', from prefix '''[[al-]]''', combining form of '''[[ad]]''', ''to'', + '''[[ludere]]''', ''play'': compare with French ''[[allusion]]''.

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌˈlu.ʒən/

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Indirect reference; a hint; a reference to something supposed to be known, but not explicitly mentioned; a covert indication.
